24/06/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The extremist group Sect of Revolutionaries has threatened new terror attacks on police and government targets in Greece, local media reported on Wednesday (June 24th). The group made the threats in a statement to the daily Ta Nea on Monday. It also claimed responsibility for last week's murder of Nektarios Savas, a police officer who was guarding the home of a witness in a terrorism trial.
In other news, a homemade bomb exploded in front of a bank in the northeastern town of Kavala on Tuesday. The blast caused property damage but no injuries. (Ta Nea, Naftemporiki, Vima, Diesi - 24/06/09; News 24/7, Zougla - 23/06/09)
